{
  "stem": "12447.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So if I saw one coming in, I would go over to him and asked him which way did you come in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then he would tell me that this guard and this and this situation, he is-- he's OK, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You, you could go there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I tried to go out through there, smuggle my way out, or go in different way through a hole or through other means of getting out of the ghetto, buying the food, and trying to come in through that gate.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a Zabowska gate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was a Leszno gate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There-- I, I can't remember all the-- all the places.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there were quite a few around Warsaw that you were able to take a tram-- I mean a streetcar-- get to that point and come in.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This go-- this went--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--on in 1940, winter, into '41 and during the summer of '41.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It kept on going on, I remember, through the whole summer into the fall of 1941.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Things were getting really harder and harder of going-- getting out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And things were getting to the point that people were really starving from hunger.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You could not find-- you know, if I can describe in brief the life in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The life in the ghetto-- whoever had something to eat survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Whoever did not have what to eat was dying of hunger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And things were-- in 1941 summer, you seen a lot of people laying in the streets, swollen from hunger.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People were dying from hunger.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Children would come-- like, you had beggars walking around and calling in the houses, can we get a-- in the beginning, can we get a, a small piece of bread from somebody?",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
